				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					For the sorting, join to the posts table and then ORDER BY the post&#39;s date.  Use GROUP BY to just get the max date.  Something like this:<br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-auto linenums:0'>
SELECT
	JobId,
	JobTitle, 
	MAX(PostedOn) as postedOn
FROM jobs
LEFT JOIN posts ON posts.JobId=jobs.JobId
GROUP BY
	JobId,
	JobTitle
ORDER BY
	postedOn
</pre><br />As for the unread indicator, you&#39;ll have to add a column to the posts table indicating whether that post is read or not.  Whenever a client views the post then update that column to indicate it has been read.  When you select your list of jobs, check for and unread rows using that column.<br />
					
					<br />
					
				</div>
				
				
